===============================================================================
 Building the Gaim iFolder Plugin (gifolder)
===============================================================================

Note for Novell Linux Desktop (NLD)
------------------------------------

	Use this revision tag: v0_82
	Use this directory name: gaim-0.82
	Use this patch file: gaim-0.82.patches


1. Checkout gaim-1.5.0 from CVS
---------------------------------

    cd ~    (Your home directory)

    cvs -d:pserver:anonymous@cvs.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/gaim login
    (Just hit enter for the password)

    cvs -z3 -d:pserver:anonymous@cvs.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/gaim checkout -r v1_5_0 -d gaim-1.5.0 gaim
    (This will checkout Gaim Version 1.5.0 into a new directory ~/gaim-1.5.0)
    

2. Patch gaim-1.5.0 so it's ready to build gifolder
----------------------------------------------------

    cd ~/gaim-1.5.0

    mkdir plugins/gifolder

    cp -r $GAIM_IFOLDER_PROJECT/gifolder/* plugins/gifolder

    patch -p0 < $GAIM_IFOLDER_PROJECT/gaim-1.5.0.patches

    -------------------
    Note to maintainer:
    -------------------
    Create the patch by checking out the desired version from gaim, modifying
    the necessary files, and then typing from the root of the gaim project:
    
    cvs diff -aur v1_5_0 > patch_file
    
    - OR -
    
    If CVS is down (which it happens to be today), untar the sourcecode in two
    different directories, modify one, and then create the patchfile by typing
    this from the root of the unmodified gaim directory:
    
    diff -aur . <modified gaim> > patch_file
    

3. Build Gaim
---------------

    cd ~/gaim-1.5.0
    
    Linux:
    ./autogen.sh
    make
    make install
    
    Win32:
    make -f Makefile.mingw install

===============================================================================

For more elaborate build instructions on how you should build Gaim, view the
instructions near the bottom of the following page:

    http://gaim.sourceforge.net/downloads.php
